JOHANNESBURG - South African Airways has warned its passengers that flights might be disrupted on Wednesday morning.In a statement, it said it had been served with a strike notice by one of the labour unions representing its cabin crew members.The airline said it is doing everything possible to reach a settlement on matters that are currently under discussion.The national carrier said preparations were under way to counter any service disruptions.It urged customers to visit its website for regular updates on all flight schedules.eNCA